Hawk flew in from north east to a tall eucalypus tree. Then, it perched for quite a while, before flying off to the west, and making a large arc around to the east, then flying off.

Woodpecker photographed was calling very loudly. Another woodpecker around nearby to the east was responding and, after around 3 minutes, the woodpecker photographed flew toward the other woodpecker calling. I heard calls for the rest of my time in the area (~15 minutes) sporadically. Based on the third photograph, I believe this individual is a male.
